title: 106_s1894

SECTION 1. CONVEYANCE OF LAND TO PARK COUNTY, WYOMING. Congress finds that over 82 percent of the land in Park County, Wyoming is owned by the Federal Government. The parcel of land in Park County has been withdrawn from the public domain for reclamation purposes and is managed by the Bureau of Reclamation. The land has undergone various surveys and assessments by the Bureau of Reclamation and the Bureau of Land Management, leading to a recommendation for disposal of the land. The County of Park County, Wyoming has shown interest in using a 190.12-acre parcel of land for local economic development. The Administrator of the General Services Administration will convey the land to the County for $240,000. The legal description of the land is provided in the document. The 190.12-acre parcel of land in Park County, Wyoming will be conveyed for $240,000. In Park County, Wyoming, a 190.12-acre parcel of land will be conveyed for $240,000.
